body:
If I annotate a function using PEP484/526 syntax

```Python
import cython

@cython.cfunc
def fib(n : cython.int) -> cython.int:
    if (n<=1):
        return n
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```

 ```cython -c``` tells me the last line interacts with Python, basically checking ```PyErr_Occurred()```. 

Whereas if I use decorators, there are no such checks, and Cython generates the same C code as it would with Pyrex syntax:

```Python
import cython

@cython.cfunc
@cython.locals(n=cython.int)
@cython.returns(cython.int)
def _fib(n):
    if (n<=1):
        return n
    return _fib(n-1) + _fib(n-2)
```

The return line using PEP484/526 syntax looks like this
```C
+08:     return _fib(n-1) + _fib(n-2)
  __pyx_t_2 = __pyx_f_46_cython_magic_dd8e3b97486038017346fa36994a0695__fib((__pyx_v_n - 1)); if (unlikely(__pyx_t_2 == ((int)-1) && PyErr_Occurred())) __PYX_ERR(0, 8, __pyx_L1_error)
  __pyx_t_3 = __pyx_f_46_cython_magic_dd8e3b97486038017346fa36994a0695__fib((__pyx_v_n - 2)); if (unlikely(__pyx_t_3 == ((int)-1) && PyErr_Occurred())) __PYX_ERR(0, 8, __pyx_L1_error)
  __pyx_r = (__pyx_t_2 + __pyx_t_3);
  goto __pyx_L0;
```

whereas with decorators it looks like this
```C
+11:     return _fib(n-1) + _fib(n-2)
  __pyx_r = (__pyx_f_46_cython_magic_6c3a15eed3bce3137103a8464b16a811__fib((__pyx_v_n - 1)) + __pyx_f_46_cython_magic_6c3a15eed3bce3137103a8464b16a811__fib((__pyx_v_n - 2)));
  goto __pyx_L0;
```

comment_data.body:
It it were documented, I would not had spent time convincing myself that is was a bug :)

In my timings for the Fibonacci toy function the exception check accounts for 10% of the run-time. I guess that is quite unsignificant as the function does not do much but recurse, add, and error check. 

Anyhow, with some experimentation I found that this combination is what is needed to make an annotated function behave like a "real" C function:

```Python
@cython.exceptval(check=False)
@cython.cfunc
@cython.nogil
def fib(n : cython.int) -> cython.int:
    if (n<=1):
        return n
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```

Maybe it should be documented to avoid any surprises.
